  "text": "The Kubernetes API deprecation policy enforcement is implemented across multiple core files in the API server codebase. The enforcement consists of three main components: deprecated API version warning injection, removal version validation, and minimum supported API version checks.\n\n## Deprecated API Version Warning Injection\n\nThe warning injection mechanism is implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/metrics/metrics.go`. This file contains:\n- `deprecatedRequestGauge`: A Prometheus gauge metric that tracks deprecated API requests with labels for group, version, resource, subresource, and removed_release\n- `deprecatedAnnotationKey` and `removedReleaseAnnotationKey` constants for audit annotations\n- `MonitorRequest()` function (line 581) that adds audit annotations when deprecated APIs are accessed\n- `InstrumentRouteFunc()` (line 624) and `InstrumentHandlerFunc()` (line 643) that wrap route handlers to record metrics and warnings for deprecated APIs\n\n## API Deprecation Logic\n\nThe core deprecation checking logic is in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/deprecation/deprecation.go`. This module provides:\n- `IsDeprecated()` function (line 63): Checks if an object implements APILifecycleDeprecated() and if the deprecation is currently active based on the current Kubernetes version\n- `RemovedRelease()` function (line 90): Returns the target removal version in \"<major>.<minor>\" format if the object implements APILifecycleRemoved()\n- `WarningMessage()` function (line 102): Generates human-readable deprecation warnings that include deprecation version, removal version, and replacement API information\n- `MajorMinor()` function (line 49): Parses version information from the API server version\n\n## Integration Point: API Installer\n\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go` file is where the deprecation checking is integrated into the request handling pipeline. In the `registerResourceHandlers()` function (around line 788-796):\n- It calls `deprecation.MajorMinor(versioninfo.Get())` to get the current API server version\n- It calls `deprecation.IsDeprecated()` to check if the API version is deprecated\n- If deprecated, it calls `deprecation.RemovedRelease()` to get the removal version\n- It calls `deprecation.WarningMessage()` to get the warning text\n- These values are then passed to `metrics.InstrumentRouteFunc()` to instrument the route handlers\n\n## Removal Version Validation & Minimum Supported Version Checks\n\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/deleted_kinds.go` file implements the removal version validation and minimum supported API version enforcement. Key components:\n\n- `ResourceExpirationEvaluator` interface: Defines methods for evaluating whether resources should be served\n- `resourceExpirationEvaluator` struct (line 41): Holds the current API server version and configuration for determining if APIs should be served\n- `ShouldServeForVersion()` (line 150): Validates removal versions by comparing the removal version with the current API server version. Returns false if the API has been removed for the current version (unless special flags like KUBE_APISERVER_SERVE_REMOVED_APIS_FOR_ONE_RELEASE or KUBE_APISERVER_STRICT_REMOVED_API_HANDLING_IN_ALPHA are set)\n- `removeDeletedKinds()` (line 184): Removes storage for resources that have reached their removal version\n- `RemoveUnavailableKinds()` (line 218): Main method that removes both deleted kinds (using APILifecycleRemoved) and unintroduced kinds (using APILifecycleIntroduced)\n- `removeUnintroducedKinds()` (line 225): Implements minimum supported API version checking by removing storage for API versions introduced after the current API server version (with emulation forward compatibility options)\n- `isNotRemoved()` (line 127): Checks if a resource is not removed based on APILifecycleRemoved information\n\n## Execution Flow\n\nWhen an API request is made:\n1. The API installer checks if the requested API version is deprecated using `deprecation.IsDeprecated()`\n2. If deprecated, it injects a warning annotation using `metrics.InstrumentRouteFunc()` which calls `MonitorRequest()`\n3. At API server startup, `RemoveUnavailableKinds()` is called to validate and remove any API versions that have reached their removal version or are introduced after the current API server version\n4. The `ShouldServeForVersion()` method enforces the removal deadline by comparing removal versions with the current API server version\n\nThese mechanisms together enforce the Kubernetes API deprecation policy by: warning users when deprecated APIs are used, validating removal deadlines, and preventing access to API versions that have been removed."
}

